<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="1" type="etymology">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Etymology.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="1">The species is named in memory of our colleague Vladimir Borisovich Shuvalikov, an entomologist, geneticist, and teacher.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="1" type="description">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Description.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
<emphasis bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Female.</emphasis>
Habitus as in Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 1" captionStartId="F1" captionText="Figure 1. Protaphycus shuvalikovi gen. et sp. nov., holotype female A body, dorsal, (cs - covering setae; fs - filum spinosum; n - notaular line; pmv - postmarginal vein; pst - parastigma; u - uncus) B body, dorsolateral, (p - pedicel). Scale bars: 0.2 mm." figureDoi="10.3897/jhr.91.81957.figure1" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/706651" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">1A, B</figureCitation>
. Body length 0.6 mm.
</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
<emphasis bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Coloration and sculpture</emphasis>
.
</emphasis>
Body, tegula, legs, gaster dorsally and ventrally black; clava darker than F6 (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 2" captionStartId="F2" captionText="Figure 2. Protaphycus shuvalikovi gen. et sp. nov., holotype female A body, posteroventral (cl - clava, ms - mesotibial spur) B body, posteroventral (cers - cercal setae, sp - spiracle on the lateral plate of the Mt 8) C gaster, posteroventrolateral (c - cercus, hyp - hypopygium - black arrow indicates the apex of the hypopygium ventraly, syn - syntergum, v 3 - ovipositor sheaths). Scale bars: 0.2 mm (A, C); 0.1 mm (B)." figureDoi="10.3897/jhr.91.81957.figure2" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/706652" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">2A</figureCitation>
); surface of frontovertex, mesoscutum, scutellum and axillae smooth, shiny (probably due to the presence of a thin layer of air), but without visible metallic shine; mesoscutum with rare black setae (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 1" captionStartId="F1" captionText="Figure 1. Protaphycus shuvalikovi gen. et sp. nov., holotype female A body, dorsal, (cs - covering setae; fs - filum spinosum; n - notaular line; pmv - postmarginal vein; pst - parastigma; u - uncus) B body, dorsolateral, (p - pedicel). Scale bars: 0.2 mm." figureDoi="10.3897/jhr.91.81957.figure1" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/706651" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">1A</figureCitation>
), ovipositor sheaths pale yellow; head, thorax, legs, and gaster shallow reticulate, but surface of head only sparsely punctate, some cells of frontovertex with one convex point (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 1" captionStartId="F1" captionText="Figure 1. Protaphycus shuvalikovi gen. et sp. nov., holotype female A body, dorsal, (cs - covering setae; fs - filum spinosum; n - notaular line; pmv - postmarginal vein; pst - parastigma; u - uncus) B body, dorsolateral, (p - pedicel). Scale bars: 0.2 mm." figureDoi="10.3897/jhr.91.81957.figure1" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/706651" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">1A</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
<emphasis bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Head</emphasis>
.
</emphasis>
Hypognathous, slightly wider than thorax in dorsal view, about 1.5 
<normalizedToken originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
as broad as long; occipital margin sharp, but not carinate (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 1" captionStartId="F1" captionText="Figure 1. Protaphycus shuvalikovi gen. et sp. nov., holotype female A body, dorsal, (cs - covering setae; fs - filum spinosum; n - notaular line; pmv - postmarginal vein; pst - parastigma; u - uncus) B body, dorsolateral, (p - pedicel). Scale bars: 0.2 mm." figureDoi="10.3897/jhr.91.81957.figure1" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/706651" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">1B</figureCitation>
); eyes clothed in sparse setae 2 
<normalizedToken originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
as long as diameter of eye facet (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 1" captionStartId="F1" captionText="Figure 1. Protaphycus shuvalikovi gen. et sp. nov., holotype female A body, dorsal, (cs - covering setae; fs - filum spinosum; n - notaular line; pmv - postmarginal vein; pst - parastigma; u - uncus) B body, dorsolateral, (p - pedicel). Scale bars: 0.2 mm." figureDoi="10.3897/jhr.91.81957.figure1" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/706651" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">1A</figureCitation>
), with inner orbits parallel; frontovertex only slightly longer than broad, almost one-third head width; ocelli in right-angled triangle, posterior ocelli elliptical in dorsal view, OOL about one-third posterior ocellus diameter (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 1" captionStartId="F1" captionText="Figure 1. Protaphycus shuvalikovi gen. et sp. nov., holotype female A body, dorsal, (cs - covering setae; fs - filum spinosum; n - notaular line; pmv - postmarginal vein; pst - parastigma; u - uncus) B body, dorsolateral, (p - pedicel). Scale bars: 0.2 mm." figureDoi="10.3897/jhr.91.81957.figure1" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/706651" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">1A, B</figureCitation>
); OCL slightly shorter than posterior ocellar diameter; OOL:POL:LOL:OCL about 1:8:5:2; eye reaching occipital margin; facial cavity, location of toruli, and interantennal prominence not visible in holotype.
</paragraph>
<caption doi="10.3897/jhr.91.81957.figure1" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/706651" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" start="Figure 1" startId="F1">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
<emphasis bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Figure 1.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName authorityName="Simutnik" authorityYear="2022" family="Encyrtidae" genus="Protaphycus" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Protaphycus shuvalikovi" order="Diptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" rank="species" species="shuvalikovi">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Protaphycus shuvalikovi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
gen. et sp. nov., holotype female 
<emphasis bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">A</emphasis>
body, dorsal, (cs - covering setae; fs -filum spinosum; n - notaular line; pmv - postmarginal vein; pst - parastigma; u - uncus) 
<emphasis bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">B</emphasis>
body, dorsolateral, (p - pedicel). Scale bars: 0.2 mm.
</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
<emphasis bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Antenna</emphasis>
.
</emphasis>
Geniculate, 11-segmented (1:1:6:3); scape long, not widened (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 1" captionStartId="F1" captionText="Figure 1. Protaphycus shuvalikovi gen. et sp. nov., holotype female A body, dorsal, (cs - covering setae; fs - filum spinosum; n - notaular line; pmv - postmarginal vein; pst - parastigma; u - uncus) B body, dorsolateral, (p - pedicel). Scale bars: 0.2 mm." figureDoi="10.3897/jhr.91.81957.figure1" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/706651" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">1B</figureCitation>
); pedicel conical, about as long as F1-F4 combined, longer than any segment of funicle, all funicular segments transverse, F1-F4 very small and subequal (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 1" captionStartId="F1" captionText="Figure 1. Protaphycus shuvalikovi gen. et sp. nov., holotype female A body, dorsal, (cs - covering setae; fs - filum spinosum; n - notaular line; pmv - postmarginal vein; pst - parastigma; u - uncus) B body, dorsolateral, (p - pedicel). Scale bars: 0.2 mm." figureDoi="10.3897/jhr.91.81957.figure1" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/706651" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">1A, B</figureCitation>
), mps not visible; F6 twice as broad as long (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 2" captionStartId="F2" captionText="Figure 2. Protaphycus shuvalikovi gen. et sp. nov., holotype female A body, posteroventral (cl - clava, ms - mesotibial spur) B body, posteroventral (cers - cercal setae, sp - spiracle on the lateral plate of the Mt 8) C gaster, posteroventrolateral (c - cercus, hyp - hypopygium - black arrow indicates the apex of the hypopygium ventraly, syn - syntergum, v 3 - ovipositor sheaths). Scale bars: 0.2 mm (A, C); 0.1 mm (B)." figureDoi="10.3897/jhr.91.81957.figure2" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/706652" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">2A</figureCitation>
); width of flagellomeres increases toward apex; at least, all segments of clava with mps (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 2" captionStartId="F2" captionText="Figure 2. Protaphycus shuvalikovi gen. et sp. nov., holotype female A body, posteroventral (cl - clava, ms - mesotibial spur) B body, posteroventral (cers - cercal setae, sp - spiracle on the lateral plate of the Mt 8) C gaster, posteroventrolateral (c - cercus, hyp - hypopygium - black arrow indicates the apex of the hypopygium ventraly, syn - syntergum, v 3 - ovipositor sheaths). Scale bars: 0.2 mm (A, C); 0.1 mm (B)." figureDoi="10.3897/jhr.91.81957.figure2" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/706652" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">2A</figureCitation>
); clava large, only slightly shorter than funicle (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 1" captionStartId="F1" captionText="Figure 1. Protaphycus shuvalikovi gen. et sp. nov., holotype female A body, dorsal, (cs - covering setae; fs - filum spinosum; n - notaular line; pmv - postmarginal vein; pst - parastigma; u - uncus) B body, dorsolateral, (p - pedicel). Scale bars: 0.2 mm." figureDoi="10.3897/jhr.91.81957.figure1" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/706651" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">1A</figureCitation>
); about 2 
<normalizedToken originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
as long as broad, with small oblique truncation (sensor region) on rounded apical segment (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 2" captionStartId="F2" captionText="Figure 2. Protaphycus shuvalikovi gen. et sp. nov., holotype female A body, posteroventral (cl - clava, ms - mesotibial spur) B body, posteroventral (cers - cercal setae, sp - spiracle on the lateral plate of the Mt 8) C gaster, posteroventrolateral (c - cercus, hyp - hypopygium - black arrow indicates the apex of the hypopygium ventraly, syn - syntergum, v 3 - ovipositor sheaths). Scale bars: 0.2 mm (A, C); 0.1 mm (B)." figureDoi="10.3897/jhr.91.81957.figure2" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/706652" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">2 A</figureCitation>
), wider than F6; flagellum and clava clothed in very short setae.
</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
<emphasis bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Mesosoma</emphasis>
.
</emphasis>
Pronotum almost vertical, with small transverse dorsal surface (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 1" captionStartId="F1" captionText="Figure 1. Protaphycus shuvalikovi gen. et sp. nov., holotype female A body, dorsal, (cs - covering setae; fs - filum spinosum; n - notaular line; pmv - postmarginal vein; pst - parastigma; u - uncus) B body, dorsolateral, (p - pedicel). Scale bars: 0.2 mm." figureDoi="10.3897/jhr.91.81957.figure1" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/706651" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">1A, B</figureCitation>
); mesoscutum broader than long, 
<normalizedToken originalValue="ﬂat">ﬂat</normalizedToken>
, notaular lines present as grooves (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 1" captionStartId="F1" captionText="Figure 1. Protaphycus shuvalikovi gen. et sp. nov., holotype female A body, dorsal, (cs - covering setae; fs - filum spinosum; n - notaular line; pmv - postmarginal vein; pst - parastigma; u - uncus) B body, dorsolateral, (p - pedicel). Scale bars: 0.2 mm." figureDoi="10.3897/jhr.91.81957.figure1" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/706651" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">1A, B</figureCitation>
: n) at extreme anterior part of mesoscutum; axillae transverse-triangular with anteromedial angles contiguous (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 1" captionStartId="F1" captionText="Figure 1. Protaphycus shuvalikovi gen. et sp. nov., holotype female A body, dorsal, (cs - covering setae; fs - filum spinosum; n - notaular line; pmv - postmarginal vein; pst - parastigma; u - uncus) B body, dorsolateral, (p - pedicel). Scale bars: 0.2 mm." figureDoi="10.3897/jhr.91.81957.figure1" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/706651" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">1A</figureCitation>
); scutellum 
<normalizedToken originalValue="ﬂat">ﬂat</normalizedToken>
, about as long as mesoscutum.
</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
<emphasis bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Wings</emphasis>
.
</emphasis>
Fully developed, forewings wide, with round apex; linea calva with filum spinosum, covering setae along basal margin of linea calva present, well developed (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 1" captionStartId="F1" captionText="Figure 1. Protaphycus shuvalikovi gen. et sp. nov., holotype female A body, dorsal, (cs - covering setae; fs - filum spinosum; n - notaular line; pmv - postmarginal vein; pst - parastigma; u - uncus) B body, dorsolateral, (p - pedicel). Scale bars: 0.2 mm." figureDoi="10.3897/jhr.91.81957.figure1" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/706651" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">1A,B</figureCitation>
: cs); area basal to covering setae bare and looking like speculum (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 1" captionStartId="F1" captionText="Figure 1. Protaphycus shuvalikovi gen. et sp. nov., holotype female A body, dorsal, (cs - covering setae; fs - filum spinosum; n - notaular line; pmv - postmarginal vein; pst - parastigma; u - uncus) B body, dorsolateral, (p - pedicel). Scale bars: 0.2 mm." figureDoi="10.3897/jhr.91.81957.figure1" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/706651" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">1A</figureCitation>
); hyaline break (unpigmented area) present; proportions of forewing venation, shape of parastigma, and setation of linea calva as in Figs 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 1" captionStartId="F1" captionText="Figure 1. Protaphycus shuvalikovi gen. et sp. nov., holotype female A body, dorsal, (cs - covering setae; fs - filum spinosum; n - notaular line; pmv - postmarginal vein; pst - parastigma; u - uncus) B body, dorsolateral, (p - pedicel). Scale bars: 0.2 mm." figureDoi="10.3897/jhr.91.81957.figure1" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/706651" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">1A,B</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 2" captionStartId="F2" captionText="Figure 2. Protaphycus shuvalikovi gen. et sp. nov., holotype female A body, posteroventral (cl - clava, ms - mesotibial spur) B body, posteroventral (cers - cercal setae, sp - spiracle on the lateral plate of the Mt 8) C gaster, posteroventrolateral (c - cercus, hyp - hypopygium - black arrow indicates the apex of the hypopygium ventraly, syn - syntergum, v 3 - ovipositor sheaths). Scale bars: 0.2 mm (A, C); 0.1 mm (B)." figureDoi="10.3897/jhr.91.81957.figure2" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/706652" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">2A</figureCitation>
; marginal vein 2 
<normalizedToken originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
as long as broad and about 1.5 as long as postmarginal (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 1" captionStartId="F1" captionText="Figure 1. Protaphycus shuvalikovi gen. et sp. nov., holotype female A body, dorsal, (cs - covering setae; fs - filum spinosum; n - notaular line; pmv - postmarginal vein; pst - parastigma; u - uncus) B body, dorsolateral, (p - pedicel). Scale bars: 0.2 mm." figureDoi="10.3897/jhr.91.81957.figure1" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/706651" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">1A,B</figureCitation>
); stigmal vein with long narrow uncus, consisting row of uncal sensilla; seta marking apex of postmarginal vein of fore wing not longer than others on the marginal and postmarginal veins; setae of marginal fringe short.
</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
<emphasis bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Legs</emphasis>
.
</emphasis>
Normal in size, alike polygonal reticulate; tarsi 5-segmented, mesotibial spur slightly longer than mesobasitarsus, both relatively short (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 2" captionStartId="F2" captionText="Figure 2. Protaphycus shuvalikovi gen. et sp. nov., holotype female A body, posteroventral (cl - clava, ms - mesotibial spur) B body, posteroventral (cers - cercal setae, sp - spiracle on the lateral plate of the Mt 8) C gaster, posteroventrolateral (c - cercus, hyp - hypopygium - black arrow indicates the apex of the hypopygium ventraly, syn - syntergum, v 3 - ovipositor sheaths). Scale bars: 0.2 mm (A, C); 0.1 mm (B)." figureDoi="10.3897/jhr.91.81957.figure2" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/706652" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">2A</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<caption doi="10.3897/jhr.91.81957.figure2" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/706652" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" start="Figure 2" startId="F2">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
<emphasis bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Figure 2.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName authorityName="Simutnik" authorityYear="2022" family="Encyrtidae" genus="Protaphycus" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Protaphycus shuvalikovi" order="Diptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" rank="species" species="shuvalikovi">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Protaphycus shuvalikovi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
gen. et sp. nov., holotype female 
<emphasis bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">A</emphasis>
body, posteroventral (cl - clava, ms - mesotibial spur) 
<emphasis bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">B</emphasis>
body, posteroventral (cers - cercal setae, sp - spiracle on the lateral plate of the Mt8) 
<emphasis bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">C</emphasis>
gaster, posteroventrolateral (c - cercus, hyp - hypopygium - black arrow indicates the apex of the hypopygium ventraly, syn - syntergum, v3 - ovipositor sheaths). Scale bars: 0.2 mm (
<emphasis bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">A, C</emphasis>
); 0.1 mm (
<emphasis bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">B</emphasis>
).
</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
<emphasis bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Gaster</emphasis>
.
</emphasis>
Polygonal reticulate equal dorsally and ventrally; apex of hypopygium sharp, distinctly reaching way past apex of syntergum (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 2" captionStartId="F2" captionText="Figure 2. Protaphycus shuvalikovi gen. et sp. nov., holotype female A body, posteroventral (cl - clava, ms - mesotibial spur) B body, posteroventral (cers - cercal setae, sp - spiracle on the lateral plate of the Mt 8) C gaster, posteroventrolateral (c - cercus, hyp - hypopygium - black arrow indicates the apex of the hypopygium ventraly, syn - syntergum, v 3 - ovipositor sheaths). Scale bars: 0.2 mm (A, C); 0.1 mm (B)." figureDoi="10.3897/jhr.91.81957.figure2" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/706652" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">2C</figureCitation>
: hyp, syn); gonostyli (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 2" captionStartId="F2" captionText="Figure 2. Protaphycus shuvalikovi gen. et sp. nov., holotype female A body, posteroventral (cl - clava, ms - mesotibial spur) B body, posteroventral (cers - cercal setae, sp - spiracle on the lateral plate of the Mt 8) C gaster, posteroventrolateral (c - cercus, hyp - hypopygium - black arrow indicates the apex of the hypopygium ventraly, syn - syntergum, v 3 - ovipositor sheaths). Scale bars: 0.2 mm (A, C); 0.1 mm (B)." figureDoi="10.3897/jhr.91.81957.figure2" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/706652" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">2C</figureCitation>
: v3) separated from apex of hypopygium; lateral margin of hypopygium bare, without row of setae; shape of hypopygium, location of cercal plates, and cercal setae as in Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 2" captionStartId="F2" captionText="Figure 2. Protaphycus shuvalikovi gen. et sp. nov., holotype female A body, posteroventral (cl - clava, ms - mesotibial spur) B body, posteroventral (cers - cercal setae, sp - spiracle on the lateral plate of the Mt 8) C gaster, posteroventrolateral (c - cercus, hyp - hypopygium - black arrow indicates the apex of the hypopygium ventraly, syn - syntergum, v 3 - ovipositor sheaths). Scale bars: 0.2 mm (A, C); 0.1 mm (B)." figureDoi="10.3897/jhr.91.81957.figure2" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/706652" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">2B, C</figureCitation>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
<emphasis bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Male.</emphasis>
Unknown.
</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
The earliest known 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Forster" baseAuthorityYear="1856" class="Insecta" family="Encyrtidae" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">Encyrtidae</taxonomicName>
include one female and four males were ascribed to five different genera from middle Eocene Sakhalinian amber (
<bibRefCitation DOI="https://doi.org/10.1080/08912963.2020.1835887" author="Simutnik, SA" journalOrPublisher="Entomological Review" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" refId="B13" refString="Simutnik, SA, 2021. https://doi.org/10.1080/08912963.2020.1835887" url="https://doi.org/10.1080/08912963.2020.1835887" year="2021">Simutnik 2021</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation DOI="https://doi.org/10.3897/jhr.84.66367" author="Simutnik, SA" journalOrPublisher="Journal of Hymenoptera Research" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" pagination="361 - 372" refId="B16" refString="Simutnik, SA, Perkovsky, EE, Vasilenko, DV, 2021a. Sakhalinencyrtus leleji Simutnik gen. et sp. nov. of earliest Encyrtidae (Hymenoptera, Chalcidoidea) from Sakhalinian amber. Journal of Hymenoptera Research 84: 361 - 372, DOI: https://doi.org/10.3897/jhr.84.66367" title="Sakhalinencyrtus leleji Simutnik gen. et sp. nov. of earliest Encyrtidae (Hymenoptera, Chalcidoidea) from Sakhalinian amber." url="https://doi.org/10.3897/jhr.84.66367" volume="84" year="2021 a">Simutnik et al. 2021a</bibRefCitation>
). They did not have the filum spinosum and differed significantly from the both extant and late Eocene European encyrtids. To date, 16 species from 14 extinct genera are described from the Rovno, Baltic, and Danish ambers. Half of them, including the 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Simutnik" authorityYear="2022" family="Encyrtidae" genus="Protaphycus" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Protaphycus shuvalikovi" order="Diptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" rank="species" species="shuvalikovi">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Protaphycus shuvalikovi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, had the filum spinosum and, putatively, belong to 
<taxonomicName lsidName="" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" rank="subFamily" subFamily="Encyrtinae">Encyrtinae</taxonomicName>
. The most of the known European amber 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Forster" baseAuthorityYear="1856" class="Insecta" family="Encyrtidae" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">Encyrtidae</taxonomicName>
differ from the majority of extant ones by the subapical position of the cerci, the relatively long marginal vein of the forewing, a distinctly swollen but not triangular parastigma, a short radicle, and by a seta marking the apex of the postmarginal vein that is not any longer than others on this vein. The 
<taxonomicName authority="Simutnik, 2015" authorityName="Simutnik" authorityYear="2015" class="Insecta" family="Encyrtidae" genus="Sulia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Sulia glaesaria" order="Coleoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="glaesaria">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Sulia glaesaria</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Simutnik, 2015 with a unique abdominal structure, a largest of the known extinct members of the family, was described from Danish amber and then reported from Rovno amber (
<bibRefCitation DOI="https://doi.org/10.15298/rusentj.24.1.07" author="Simutnik, SA" journalOrPublisher="Russian Entomological Journal" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" pagination="73 - 75" refId="B11" refString="Simutnik, SA, 2015a. A new fossil genus of Encyrtidae (Hymenoptera: Chalcidoidea) from late Eocene Danish amber. Russian Entomological Journal 24 (1): 73 - 75, DOI: https://doi.org/10.15298/rusentj.24.1.07" title="A new fossil genus of Encyrtidae (Hymenoptera: Chalcidoidea) from late Eocene Danish amber." url="https://doi.org/10.15298/rusentj.24.1.07" volume="24" year="2015 a">Simutnik 2015a</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation DOI="https://doi.org/10.3897/jhr.88.75941" author="Simutnik, SA" journalOrPublisher="Journal of Hymenoptera Research" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" pagination="85 - 102" refId="B17" refString="Simutnik, SA, Perkovsky, EE, Khomych, MR, Vasilenko, DV, 2021b. First record of the Sulia glaesaria Simutnik, 2015 (Hymenoptera, Chalcidoidea, Encyrtidae) from Rovno amber. Journal of Hymenoptera Research 88: 85 - 102, DOI: https://doi.org/10.3897/jhr.88.75941" title="First record of the Sulia glaesaria Simutnik, 2015 (Hymenoptera, Chalcidoidea, Encyrtidae) from Rovno amber." url="https://doi.org/10.3897/jhr.88.75941" volume="88" year="2021 b">Simutnik et al. 2021b</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
A comparative morphological analysis of the paleontological data allowed tracing character changes in some morphological structures in members of the family from the middle Eocene, through the late Eocene, to the present (
<bibRefCitation DOI="https://doi.org/10.1080/08912963.2020.1835887" author="Simutnik, SA" journalOrPublisher="Entomological Review" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" refId="B13" refString="Simutnik, SA, 2021. https://doi.org/10.1080/08912963.2020.1835887" url="https://doi.org/10.1080/08912963.2020.1835887" year="2021">Simutnik 2021</bibRefCitation>
). However, further analysis is required to determine the place of these fossil on the phylogenetic tree.
</paragraph>
